Maiek.

00:38:15.090 --> 00:38:17.460
Our bar is pretty popular, huh?

00:38:18.200 --> 00:38:20.410
Yeah. Even though it's not the high season,

00:38:20.410 --> 00:38:22.020
we still get a steady flow of customers.

00:38:22.020 --> 00:38:24.370
Why is that? Because of the mermaid legend?

00:38:24.370 --> 00:38:27.732
Whoa, you know about that?

00:38:27.732 --> 00:38:29.860
All the customers talk about it.

00:38:29.860 --> 00:38:34.190
They say that on Koh Khen,
merfolk still live among humans.

00:38:34.190 --> 00:38:37.600
They have the same appearance
and live the same way we do,

00:38:37.600 --> 00:38:39.873
so no one can tell the difference.

00:38:39.873 --> 00:38:42.503
You seem to know a lot about it.

00:38:42.503 --> 00:38:44.653
On the night before a full moon,

00:38:44.653 --> 00:38:49.313
an eight-pointed star is supposed to appear
on each of their bodies.

00:38:49.313 --> 00:38:51.113
- The night before the full moon?
- That's right.

00:38:51.113 --> 00:38:52.610
Yeah.

00:38:53.470 --> 00:38:57.610
♫ Y'all been waiting, y'all been waiting for me ♫

00:38:57.610 --> 00:38:59.740
So do you believe in it, Phu?

00:39:01.533 --> 00:39:03.933
Everyone asks me that same question.

00:39:03.933 --> 00:39:06.480
You want to know what I tell them?

00:39:06.480 --> 00:39:11.570
If someone can show me a real, live mermaid, then I'll believe them.

00:39:11.570 --> 00:39:12.800
I get it.

00:39:12.800 --> 00:39:16.050
♫ When I hear it coming up like that ♫

00:39:16.050 --> 00:39:17.470
Hello.

00:39:19.900 --> 00:39:21.780
- Hey, Maiek.
-Yes?

00:39:21.780 --> 00:39:23.140
Close up the bar for me, will you?

00:39:23.140 --> 00:39:24.730
I'm going to take some customers out.

00:39:24.730 --> 00:39:26.059
Okay.

00:39:26.059 --> 00:39:27.930
- I'll take care of it.
- Thanks.

00:39:27.930 --> 00:39:29.192
- No problem.
- And clear my glass for me.

00:39:29.192 --> 00:39:31.095
You got it.

00:39:31.095 --> 00:39:33.380
He doesn't even clear his own glass.

00:40:36.100 --> 00:40:38.790
Hey, Nava. Are you heading back?

00:40:38.790 --> 00:40:40.830
I can give you a ride.

00:40:40.830 --> 00:40:44.146
Could I just sit here for a little longer?

00:40:44.146 --> 00:40:47.690
Okay, then. I'll wait for you on the shore.

00:40:47.690 --> 00:40:49.620
Okay.

00:40:49.620 --> 00:40:51.290
See you in a bit.

00:40:52.170 --> 00:40:53.660
I'm heading off.

00:41:21.260 --> 00:41:24.050
How long has it been
since I've been this drunk?

00:41:46.277 --> 00:41:47.830
A merman.

